REFERENCE DETAILS (API signatures, exact behaviors, patterns)
- String.prototype.charAt(index?: number) -> string
  - Returns exactly one UTF-16 code unit or empty string
  - index converted to integer, undefined becomes 0
  - May return lone surrogates for broken surrogate pairs

- String.prototype.charCodeAt(index: number) -> number
  - Returns UTF-16 code unit value 0-65535
  - Returns NaN for out-of-bounds index
  - Not surrogate-pair-aware

- String.prototype.codePointAt(pos: number) -> number | undefined  
  - Returns full Unicode code point value
  - Handles surrogate pairs automatically
  - Returns undefined for out-of-bounds position

- String.prototype.normalize(form?: 'NFC'|'NFD'|'NFKC'|'NFKD') -> string
  - Returns Unicode normalized string
  - Default form may vary by implementation, specify explicitly

- String iteration patterns
  - for (const char of str): iterates by Unicode code points
  - [...str]: creates array of Unicode code points
  - Array.from(str): creates array of Unicode code points

- Intl.Segmenter API (when available)
  - new Intl.Segmenter(locale, {granularity: 'grapheme'|'word'|'sentence'})
  - segmenter.segment(text) returns iterator over segments

